component.kanban.desc: "Kanban" configuration is based on "Task". Setting Kanban as the default view brings more flexibility to workflows. Kanban can also be used by teams to collaborate on or manage tasks.
component.default_issue_type_desc: The "Custom issue type" component is automatically generated from the issue type you create, and can be placed under the navigation or subnavigation bar.
component.defect_desc: The "Bug" component contains a list of bugs, and allows you to link them to requirements and perform other operations.
component.deliverable_desc: The "Deliverable" component lists all deliverables of a project and their sources.
component.document_desc: The "Project page" component syncs page information by linking Wiki spaces.
component.file_desc: The "attachment" component lists the attachments in all issues under a project.
component.filter_desc: The "Filter" component provides three shared views — "All issues", "Assigned to me", and "Watch" — to allow you to quickly find the issues you want to view and manage.
component.folder_desc: The "Navigation" component is an empty folder. You can customize its name and the subnavigation components in it.
component.gantt_chart_desc: The "Timeline" component displays the execution sequence, duration, and progress of issues under the current project, and supports project milestone planning. It plays an important role in waterfall project management.
component.member_desc: The "Members" component lists members and their roles under the current project.
component.milestone_desc: The "Milestone" component shows the milestone timeline and list, and allows you to add, delete, modify, and view milestones, or compare historical versions.
component.module_desc: The "Module" component is used to manage product modules, and categorize issues under the modules.
component.needs_desc: The "Requirement" component contains a list of requirements, and allows you to plan and split requirements, link them to issues, and perform other operations.
component.pipeline_desc: The "Pipeline" component displays the information and updates of pipelines linked to the current project.
component.plan_desc: The "Sprint plan" component displays the stages and basic information of multiple sprints through lists and details views. It enables you to plan sprints and keep track of the progress of sprints.
component.ppm_task_desc: The "Execution" component lists all plans generated after breaking down a project plan.
component.project_desc: The "Project overview" component displays the basic project information and progress of sprints and issues under the current project.
component.project_schedule_desc: The "Project plan" component contains project plans and milestones, and supports plan breakdown through WBS as well as the comparison between historical versions of project plans.
component.publish_desc: The "Release" component contains a list of releases and supports release planning and management.
component.report_desc: The "Report" component provides multi-dimensional statistics for the current project.
component.sprint_desc: The "Sprint" component is a key component for agile development and provides information such as sprint list, sprint duration, burndown charts, and related issues.
component.task_desc: The "Task" component contains a list of tasks, and allows you to link them to issues and perform other operations.
component.todo_desc: The "Backlog" component lists to-dos and supports sprint/release planning. It is an important requirement management tool in agile development. Through drag-and-drop, a product owner can plan a sprint by adding to-dos with higher priority (such as requirements) to a sprint, or plan a release by adding to-dos to it.
component.url_desc: The "Web link" component is used to configure a URL for redirection to a webpage.
component.user_story_desc: The "User story" component lists user stories and allows you to sort and filter user stories. In addition, you can plan user stories and split development tasks under them.
component.version_desc: The "Version" component displays the versions linked to the current product and supports version management.
component.work_order_desc: The "Ticket" component is used to collect and manage tickets, assign ticket processors, and customize workflow status transitions.
container.project.agile_project.desc: With built-in agile development management components, you can easily manage sprints, assign requirements, manage bugs, and learn about the project progress in real time by using all kinds of reports.
container.project.general_project.desc: Easy-to-use general task processing templates are available for activity management.
container.project.waterfall_project.desc: With built-in project planning components, you can easily plan project milestones, break down tasks with WBS, and learn about the project progress in real time by using gantt charts.
container.project.kanban.desc: Track, collaborate on and make progress in tasks as a team. Covers various collaboration scenaries including team development and requirement management.

export_activity.table_desc:
For both predecessor and successor, four types are available: Start-Start (SS), Start-Finish (SF), Finish-Start (FS), and Finish-Finish (FF). A number followed by the predecessor/successor type indicates the dependency between objects. For example, 
for a predecessor, 2FS indicates that the current object can be started only when the No.2 object is finished; for a successor, 2FS indicates that the No.2 object can be started only when the current object is finished.

import_activities.desc.field.nodeID: Rules: input "1" for the first element at the topmost hierarchy level, then "1.1" for the first element in the next level, and "1.2" for the second element in that level, etc. Top-level elements must be plans or milestones; the elements in levels under an issue must be sub-issues.
import_activities.desc.field.assign: Input the nickname or email of users in the project (for example: zhangsan@gmail.com). If there are multiple users with the same nickname, select the one that joined the project first. Please make sure to provide correct information for each row, or the entire row will be skipped.
import_activities.desc.field.pre_depende: There are four types of predecessor dependencies: Start-to-Start (SS), Start-to-Finish (SF), Finish-to-Start (FS) and Finish-to-Finish (FF). Use numbers and predecessor identifiers to represent predecessor dependencies between objects (for example: 3FF, 5FS); when the predecessor is a milestone, the dependency must be FS or FF. If only numbers are provided here, the dependency will be FS by default.
import_activities.desc.field.post_depend: There are four types of successor dependencies: Start-to-Start (SS), Start-to-Finish (SF), Finish-to-Start (FS) and Finish-to-Finish (FF). Use numbers and successor identifiers to represent successor dependencies between objects (for example: 3FF, 5FS); when the successor is a milestone, the dependency must be SF or FF. If only numbers are provided here, the dependency will be FS by default.
import_activities.desc.field.progress: Input an integer between 0 and 100. For example: 50.

perf_announcement_content: If "ONES Performance" is enabled and fields such as "Found in production" and "Story point" have not been configured before, some reports may not be normally displayed due to insufficient data. "ONES Performance" will automatically collect data generated in the work process. Generally, reports can function normally after a sprint is complete. Every report describes how the indicators are calculated.
perf_defect_avg_duration_desc: View the average bug response and resolution time of the selected department/project/user in the specified time range. This indicator measures the team's bug response and resolution speed.
perf_defect_create_solve_trend_desc: View the bugs created and resolved by the team within the specified time range.
perf_defect_escape_detect_desc:
Bug detection rate measures the capability of a team to detect bugs by themselves. Bug escape rate measures the number and severity of bugs escaping to the next stage. Calculation method: 
Bug detection rate = number of bugs found internally * weight / [(number of bugs found internally * weight + number of bugs found by users * weight)] * 100%
Bug escape rate = number of bugs found by users * weight / [(number of bugs found internally * weight + number of bugs found by users * weight)] * 100%
Use these two indicators for analysis: 
1. If the bug detection rate is high and the escape rate is low, it means that most bugs have been found in the development stage, with great quality assurance from the test team.
2. If both bug detection rate and escape rate are high, it means that the developers need to improve their sense of built-in quality, or the testers need to improve their capabilities and professional skills. Further analysis is required based on actual conditions.
3. If the bug detection rate is low and the escape rate is high, it means that the testers need to improve their capabilities or professional skills. Further analysis is required based on actual conditions.
4. If both the bug detection rate and the escape rate are low, it means that the built-in quality practices are followed, or the functions of this version are simple.
perf_defect_ng_rate_desc: View the regression bugs of the selected department/project/user within the specified time range. Analyze and compare the development quality by projects.
perf_demand_delivery_situation_desc: View the requirements delivered on time of the selected department/project/user within the specified time range. Requirements delivered on time: Requirements with the latest "Done" status time being no later than the "Due date" or "Planned end date".
perf_issue_resp_duration_desc: View the average issue response time of the entire team in the specified time range.
perf_issue_survival_duration_desc: View the average issue age of the entire team in the specified time range.
perf_manhour_comparison_desc:
View the deviation between time estimated and actual time spent for the selected department/project/user within the specified time range. If the time estimated is less than the actual time spent, the deviation rate is a negative value; if the time estimated is more than the actual time spent, the deviation rate is a positive value. Use this indicator for analysis: 
1. Has the team effectively evaluated the development risks? Under- or over-estimation of time should be avoided.
 2. Has the promised scope been changed?
 3. Did the team encounter any challenging technical debts that caused the time spent to exceed the time estimated?
perf_sprint_delivery_situation_desc: View the sprint delivered on time of the selected department/project/user within the specified time range. Sprint delivered on time: Sprints completed before or on the "Planned end date".
perf_story_point_completed_amount_desc:
View the completed story points of the selected department/project/user within the specified time range. Use this indicator for analysis: 
1. Compare the story points completed by different departments.
 2. Compare the story points consumed by different projects.
 3. Compare the story points completed by different members.
 4. Check whether the team's worklog is appropriate.

sample_data.com.project.1: Sample project for new product development
sample_data.com.project.announcement:
{"content": "

 

  • This is a sample project to give you an insight into the development management features in ONES.
    • In Overview, you can configure key charts and information and sync them with your teams.
    • In Requirement, you can create, break down, and manage requirements.
    • In Sprint, you can plan sprint requirements, break down development tasks, as well as creating and linking test cases. During development, Kanban boards and burndown charts enable you to track progress and record task time.
    • In Report, you can analyze development efficiency via reports and charts. In Settings, you can configure a report's key fields, permissions, automated workflows, notifications, and reminders.
    • Meanwhile, you can also view other sample data in ONES Wiki, ONES TestCase, and ONES Automation.
  • To delete this sample project, go to Setting > Project operation > Delete project.

 

","project_uuid":"%s"}
